main event: A sighting of a possible lenticular saucer was reported on September 19, 1962 in Fairfield, Iowa.
interesting points: The object was described as bright and smaller than the stars., It suddenly climbed at tremendous speed and faded in the distance., The object was solid and emitted no sound., Witnesses noted that it turned and became all light., The sighting lasted approximately 4-5 minutes.
witness description: One witness who worked as a painter
